  "description": "Arthritis is a group of diseases that cause inflammation, degeneration or damage in the joints, which are the points where two bones meet. It commonly leads to joint pain, stiffness, swelling and reduced range of motion. Arthritis can affect any joint in the body but most frequently occurs in the hands, wrists, knees, hips, feet, ankles, shoulders and lower back. The condition may develop due to age-related wear and tear, autoimmune reactions, metabolic abnormalities or joint injuries.",

