  "description": "Gallstones are hardened deposits of digestive fluid (bile) that form in the gallbladder or bile ducts. The gallbladder stores bile produced by the liver, which helps digest fats. Gallstones develop when substances in bile such as cholesterol or bilirubin become concentrated and crystallize into stones. Many people with gallstones may not experience symptoms, but when a stone blocks a bile duct it can cause severe abdominal pain and digestive complications.",

